Package zone.berna.datatablesajax

Class TableResponseGenerator<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • zone.berna.datatablesajax.TableResponseGenerator<E>

  • public class TableResponseGenerator<E>
extends java.lang.Object
    Class that generates a TableResponse given a TableRequest, functions to retrieve counters and elements, and an array of the fields used as columns.

        public TableResponseGenerator.PaginatedSearchFunctionReceiver totalFilteredFunction​(@NonNull
                                                                                    TotalFilteredFunction totalFilteredFunction)

        Sets the function that retrieves the total number of entries matching the given query string, which is always trimmed, lowercase and never null.

        Calling the given function with an empty query string must return the same value as the supplier passed to totalCountSupplier.

        Parameters:
        totalFilteredFunction - the function
        Returns:
        the receiver for the function that returns the request interval of fields, the next step for building a TableResponse

      • paginatedSearchFunction

        Sets the Function that returns the requested interval of (filtered) elements, sorted by the given field, in ascending/descending order. The query string is always trimmed and in lowercase. An empty query string should return the interval of all elements.

        Returns:
        the receiver for the field name array, the next step for building a TableResponse

      • generateResponse

        @Deprecated
public TableResponse generateResponse​(TableRequest tableRequest,
                                      java.util.function.LongSupplier totalCountSupplier,
                                      TotalFilteredFunction totalFilteredFunction,
                                      PaginatedSearchFunction<E> paginatedSearchFunction,
                                      java.lang.String... fields)
        Deprecated. use builder() and its steps instead
        Generates a TableResponse given a TableRequest, functions to retrieve counters and elements, and an array of the fields used as columns.
        Parameters:
        tableRequest - the TableRequest received from the view
        totalCountSupplier - a Supplier that retrieves the total count of entries in the table
        totalFilteredFunction - a Function that returns the count of entries matching the given query string.

        The query string is always non-null, trimmed and in lowercase.

        An empty query string should result in the same value returned by totalCountSupplier

        paginatedSearchFunction - a Function that returns the requested interval of (filtered) elements, sorted by the given field, in ascending/descending order. The query string is always trimmed and in lowercase. An empty query string should return the interval of all elements
        fields - an array of field names of the element used in the table, in the same order of the columns
        Returns:
        the TableResponse instance, which should be returned to the view as a JSON response object
